Q.3) write a program to calculate area of circle (value of pi and square of radius)

Ans:-// area of circle
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    float radius;
    printf("enter radius");
    scanf("%f", &radius);
    
    printf("area is : %f" , 3.14 * radius * radius);
    
    return 0;
}

explaination:-

float        -have enough size of 4 bytes 
//            -for a statement
scanf     -to take input
%f          -defines that side is real number
&            -shows the location of variable  

(note:- you can get only 2 values after dot in output by simply typing .2 between % and f in printf line of second last )
